king-class youths, Childs looks at street culture, commercial entertainments, and youth groups and movements and finds that each influenced the emergence of a more cohesive and class-conscious working class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356346940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773563469423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773563469/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles